members.name: Rami Abdou
members.bio: My major is Computer Science, and I am currently serving as one of URMC’s Co-Presidents. I want to merge my passion for coding and product development with my love for the URM community, especially at Cornell. I hope that I can take what I’ve learned in my CIS courses and use it to inspire others to create community impact. If you at all related to my interests and goals, please reach out to me because I have a dope side project in the works right now!

members.name: Tewodros 'Tedi' Mitiku
members.bio: I am a freshman in the College of Engineering studying Computer Science with a plan to minor in either Business or Philosophy. I grew up in Northern Virginia, right outside of D.C and have always maintained a burning passion for Computer Science and technology. In addition to CS, I love music, culture, philosophy, and lifting. So if I'm not in a class, grinding at Uris, sleeping in Donlon, golfing at Robert Trent, eating at Appel, or lifting at Teagle, then I'm usually walking to one of those places.
